data.description:
Homes like this don't come up often in the heart of Canton South! This charming three-bedroom, two-bath bungalow has been thoughtfully updated throughout. Boasting 1530 square feet, the home retains it's classic charm while also being able to cater to the demands of contemporary lifestyles.

As you step into the main living room you get a sense of what to expect. A newly redesigned fireplace area flows well towards the kitchen/dining area thanks to all new flooring throughout. The open-concept design in the next few rooms is truly the heart of the home, with a seamless addition off the back that floods the space with natural light and additional living area. The updated kitchen becomes the main focal point of the area thanks to it's new cabinets and ceramic floors. The dining area offers both a breakfast bar as well as space for a lager formal table. Step down to the carpeted family room and you can see why this area offers a layout that will cater to any new owners demands. 

Down the hall you're welcomed by updated flooring and neutral colors. The first of two full baths has been well updated and is situated perfectly for both of the first floor bedrooms. Upstairs you will find a third bedroom, also offering the neutral carpet and inviting color schemes. But it's not just the cosmetics that have been updated here, the home benefits from a replaced roof, well, furnace, hot water tank, softener, and appliances within the last 7 years.

Need more space? The basement is nearly finished and offers a full bathroom and laundry as well. Once the weather breaks you'll have a spacious covered deck that leads to the built in firepit out back. Not only is this home ready and waiting for it's next owner, but it offers flexibility in how that next owner chooses to use all the different areas. 

Located in the Canton Local area, this bungalow is surrounded by local amenities, schools, parks and easy access to highways for quick commutes.
